"Gazprom is scheduled to start supplying gas to Europe via Nord Stream on Thursday after maintenance, but the Europeans themselves do not believe that supplies will be resumed and are preparing for a cold winter after a hot summer.   
  
European Commission spokesman Eric Mamer: We are working on the worst possible scenario, this scenario assumes that Gazprom will no longer supply gas to Europe... We are preparing for the winter period based on this scenario
  
Alexei Grivach, Deputy Head of the National Energy Security Fund: If these fears come true, the EU will not be able to quickly substitute the volume of Russian gas, while the available alternatives are already fully engaged

But even if the Nord Stream starts working again on July 21, Gazprom will only be able to use 40% of it, because the Siemens turbine needed for this has not been returned amid sanctions.

Daily nursery rhymes over the fakap "self-propelled grandfather on punched cards" is, of course, a sign of either a complete, on the verge of idiocy, misunderstanding of the situation. Or deliberate sabotage.

I do not agree with my colleague that Biden decides everything himself. He is certainly a fighter, and an experienced politician. But he is very old and sick. But the team that works with him is really quite good. It is fundamentally wrong to think that the team is crazy Kamala Harris. The team is people who worked for Bush Jr. and Obama. Which, under current conditions, may not be as effective as in 2002, but they will definitely drink our blood.

Well, besides that. There is the president's team, and there are influence groups that plan 40 years ahead, and it doesn't matter who the presidents will be there. For example, such an agreement as AUKUS has been prepared for more than one year. The presidents changed, and the documents on the agreement, its details continued to be discussed.

Old elite families, elite groups, business clans, where there are no strangers (what it is, you can understand, say, by reading the biography of not the biggest political player, the creator of Blackwater, Eric Prince), will not let America collapse, no matter how much you fall from your bike old president. And, I repeat, they will do everything possible to release our guts.

Yes, the US today is very different from what it was 30 years ago. BLM, leftist agenda, LGBT, police on their knees in front of blacks, leaving Afghanistan, which is still a Serbian defeat (the Taliban threw the State Department, this is clearly not a victory). But America is strong. Here, Mike Tyson is not young, he smoked, drank and sniffed. And which of you will stand with him in the ring?
The same with the United States.

And instead of stupid gurgling over Biden, it's better to talk about yourself. For example, how did we manage to bring the UAV situation to the point where it is now?

Or, say, how are we going to solve the problem of unemployment after the Western companies leave?

I would suggest that those who are passionately discussing America still focus on us. Although it is more difficult. And it takes intelligence.
